KW  - Going public
KW  - Underpricing
KW  - International financial markets
KW  - jel
AB  - The underpricing of initial public offerings is a well documented phenomenon for almost every equity market that has been examined. In Switzerland for a sample of 42 stocks that were issued in the market between 1983 and 1989 a 35.8 percent average initial return between the offering price and the closing price on the first trading day is found. In Switzerland the excess returns from offering price persist for at least three years, however if the purchase is made at the first day's closing price then the three year returns are negative. The paper discusses special institutional settings in the Swiss stock market and provides some explanations implying that underpricing can be regarded as an equilibrium situation.
ER  - 

