AB  - This paper examines the ex ante mean-variance efficiency of four alternative benchmark portfolios within a UK context. Each of the benchmark portfolios is shown to be mean-variance inefficient over the period January 1980 to December 1989. Additionally the Gibbons et al. test statistic of efficiency appears to be fairly robust to violations in the distributional assumptions (Gibbons M.R., S.A. Ross and J. Shanken, 1989, Test of the efficiency of a given portfolio, Econometrica 57, 1121–1152).
